obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (1735)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=1735&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Coastal Aquaculture Authority`
  line `Act, 2005.`
  line
  line `(2) Provisions of section 27 shall come into force at once and the remaining provisions of this Act`
  line `shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.16th December, 2005, ss. 2 to 26 (both inclusive), vide notification No. S.O. 1771(E), dated 16th December, 2005, see Gazette`
  line `of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (1736)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=1736&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Authority" means the Coastal Aquaculture Authority established under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) "coastal aquaculture" means culturing, under controlled conditions in ponds, pens, enclosures`
  line `or otherwise, in coastal areas, of shrimp, prawn, fish or any other aquatic life in saline or brackish`
  line `water; but does not include fresh water aquaculture;`
  line
  line `(d) "coastal area" means the area declared as the Coastal Regulation Zone, for the time being, in`
  line `the notification of the Government of India in the Ministry of Environment and Forests (Department`
  line `of Environment, Forests and Wildlife) No. S.O. 114(E), dated the 19th February, 1991 and includes`
  line `such other area as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify;`
  line
  line `(e) "member" means the member of the Authority appointed under sub-section (3) of section 4`
  line `and includes the Chairperson and the member-secretary;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "regulations" means the regulations made by the Authority under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Environment (Protection)`
  line `Act, 1986 (29 of 1986) shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (1737)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power of Central Government to take measures to protect environment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=1737&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government shall take all such measures as it deems necessary or expedient for regulation of coastal`
  line `aquaculture by prescribing guidelines, to ensure that coastal aquaculture does not cause any detriment to`
  line `the coastal environment and the concept of responsible coastal aquaculture contained in such guidelines`
  line `shall be followed in regulating the coastal aquaculture activities to protect the livelihood of various`
  line `sections of the people living in the coastal areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (1738)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment of Authority and appointment of Chairperson and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=1738&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect`
  line `from such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this`
  line `behalf, there shall be established for the purposes of this Act an Authority to be called the Coastal`
  line `Aquaculture Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The head office of the Authority shall be at such place as the Central Government may decide.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall consist of the following members who shall be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson who is, or has been, a Judge of a High Court;`
  line
  line `(b) one member who is an expert in the field of coastal aquaculture;`
  line
  line `(c) one member who is an expert in the field of coastal ecology nominated by the Department of`
  line `Ocean Development of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) one member who is an expert in the field of environment protection or pollution control`
  line `nominated by the Ministry of Environment and Forests of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) one member to represent the Ministry of Agriculture of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(f) one member to represent the Ministry of Commerce of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(g) four members to represent the coastal States on rotation basis;`
  line
  line `(h) one member-secretary.`
  line
  line `(4) The term of office of the Chairperson and every other member shall be three years.`
  line
  line `(5) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (1739)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Disqualifications for appointment as member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=1739&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be disqualified for being`
  line `appointed as a member if he--`
  line
  line `(a) has been convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(b) is an undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(c) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(d) has been removed or dismissed from the service of the Government or a Corporation owned`
  line `or controlled by the Government; or`
  line
  line `(e) has, in the opinion of the Central Government, such financial or other interest in the Authority`
  line `as is likely to affect prejudicially the discharge by him of his functions as a member.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (1740)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Eligibility of member for reappointment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=1740&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Subject to sub-section (5) of section 4, any person`
  line `ceasing to be a member shall be eligible for reappointment as such member for not more than two`
  line `consecutive terms.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (1741)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Meetings of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=1741&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Authority shall meet at such times and places and shall observe`
  line `such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum`
  line `thereat) as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) If for any reason the Chairperson is unable to attend any meeting of the Authority any other`
  line `member chosen by the members present at the meeting shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Authority shall be decided by a majority`
  line `of votes of the members present and voting and in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairperson or in`
  line `his absence the person presiding, shall have and exercise a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (77460)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 8
  title `Committees of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=77460&sectionno=7A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (1742)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Vacancy in Authority not to invalidate proceeding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=1742&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the Authority shall`
  line `be invalidated merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Authority; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure adopted by the Authority not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (1743)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Appointment of officers, consultants and other employees of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=1743&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes`
  line `of discharging its functions, the Authority shall appoint such number of officers and other employees as it`
  line `may consider necessary on such terms and conditions as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority may appoint, from time to time, any person as adviser or consultant as it may`
  line `consider necessary on such terms and conditions as may be specified by the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (77461)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 11
  title `Secretary of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=77461&sectionno=9A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (1744)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 12
  title `Authentication of orders and other instruments of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=1744&sectionno=10&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `All orders, decisions and other`
  line `instruments of the Authority shall be authenticated under the signature of the Chairperson or any other`
  line `member or any officer of the Authority authorised by the Chairperson in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (1745)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Functions of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=1745&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any guidelines issued by the Central Government under`
  line `section 3, the Authority shall exercise the following powers and perform the following functions,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to make regulations for the construction and operation of aquaculture farms within the coastal`
  line areas;
  line
  line `(b) to inspect coastal aquaculture farms with a view to ascertaining their environmental impact`
  line `caused by coastal aquaculture;`
  line
  line `(c) to register coastal aquaculture farms;`
  line
  line `(d) to order removal or demolition of any coastal aquaculture farms which is causing pollution`
  line `after hearing the occupier of the farm; and`
  line
  line `(e) to perform such other functions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Authority orders removal or demolition of any coastal aquaculture farm under clause`
  line `(d) of sub-section (1), the workers of the said farm shall be paid such compensation as may be settled`
  line `between the workers and the management through an authority consisting of one person only to be`
  line `appointed by the Authority and such authority may exercise such powers of a District Magistrate for such`
  line `purpose, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (1746)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to enter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=1746&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rule made in this behalf, any person generally or specially`
  line `authorised by the Authority in this behalf, may, wherever it is necessary to do so for any purposes of this`
  line `Act, at all reasonable times, enter on any coastal aquaculture land, pond, pen or enclosure and--`
  line
  line `(a) make any inspection, survey, measurement, valuation or inquiry;`
  line
  line `(b) remove or demolish any structure therein; and`
  line
  line `(c) do such other acts or things as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such person shall enter on any coastal aquaculture land, pond, pen or enclosure`
  line `without giving the occupier of such aquaculture land, pond, pen or enclosure at least twenty-four hours'`
  line `notice in writing of his intention to do so.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (77464)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 15
  title `Prohibition of certain materials.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=77464&sectionno=12A&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (1747)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `Registration for coastal aquaculture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120&sectionId=1747&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00004_200524_1517807323120
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, no person`
  line `shall carry on, or cause to be carried on, coastal aquaculture in coastal area or traditional coastal`
  line `aquaculture in the traditional coastal aquaculture farm which lies within the Coastal Regulation Zone`
  line `referred to in sub-section (9) and is not used for coastal aquaculture purposes on the appointed day unless`
  line `he has registered his farm with the Authority under sub-section (5) or in pursuance of sub-section (9), as`
  line `the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a person engaged in coastal aquaculture,`
  line `immediately before the appointed day, may continue to carry on such activity without such registration`
  line `for a period of three months from that day and if he makes an application for such registration under`
  line `sub-section (4) within the said period of three months, till the communication to him of the disposing of`
  line `such application by the Authority`
  line
  line `(3) The registration made under sub-section (5) or in pursuance of sub-section (9)`
  line
  line `(a) shall be valid for a period of five years;`
  line
  line `(b) may be renewed from time to time for a like period; and`
  line
  line `(c) shall be in such form and shall be subject to such conditions as may be specified by the`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(4) A person who intends to carry on coastal aquaculture shall make an application for registration of`
  line `his farm before the Authority in such form accompanied with such fees as may be prescribed for the`
  line `purpose of registration under sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of an application for registration of a farm under sub-section (4), the Authority shall`
  line `consider the application in the prescribed manner and after considering the application either register the`
  line `farm or reject the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority shall not reject the application without recording the reason for such`
  line rejection.
  line
  line `(6) The Authority shall, after registering a farm under sub-section (5), issue a certificate of`
  line `registration in the prescribed form to the person who has made the application for such registration.`
  line
  line `(7) In the case of a farm comprising more than two hectares of water spread area, no application for`
  line `registration to commence any activity connected with coastal aquaculture shall be considered under`
  line `sub-section (5) unless the Authority, after making such inquiry as it thinks fit, is satisfied that registration`
  line `of such farm shall not be detrimental to the coastal environment.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) no coastal aquaculture shall be carried on within two hundred metres from High Tide Lines;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) no coastal aquaculture shall be carried on in creeks, rivers and backwaters within the Coastal`
  line `Regulation Zone declared for the time being under the Environment (Protection) Act,`
  line `1986 (29 of 1986):`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply in the case of a coastal aquaculture farm which is`
  line `in existence on the appointed day and to the non-commercial and experimental coastal aquaculture farms`
  line `operated or proposed to be operated by any research institute of the Government or funded by the`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Authority may, for the purposes of providing exemption under the first`
  line `proviso, review from time to time the existence and activities of the coastal aquaculture farms and the`
  line `provisions of this section shall apply on coastal aquaculture farms in view of such review.`
  line
  line `Explanation. For the purposes of this sub-section, "High Tide Line" means the line on the land up`
  line `to which the highest water line reaches during the spring tide.`
  line
  line `(9) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, any traditional coastal aquaculture farm which`
  line `lies within the Coastal Regulation Zone declared by the notification of the Government of India in the`
  line `Ministry of Environment and Forest (Department of Environment, Forests and Wildlife) No.S.O.114(E),`
  line `dated the 19th February, 1991 and is not used for coastal aquaculture purposes on the appointed day shall`
  line `be registered under sub-section (5) by producing before the Authority, by the person who is the owner of`
  line `such farm, the documentary proof of such ownership failing which such farm shall not be registered under`
  line `sub-section (5) and if such person after such registration does not utilise such farm, within one year, for`
  line `coastal aquaculture purposes, the registration shall be cancelled by the Authority.`
  line
  line `(10) A person, who intends to renew the registration of a farm made under sub-section (5) or in`
  line `pursuance of sub-section (9), may make an application within two months before the expiry of such`
  line `registration to the Authority in the prescribed form accompanied with the prescribed fees and the`
  line `Authority shall, after receiving such application, renew the registration and for such purpose make an`
  line `entry with its seal on the registration certificate relating to such form issued under sub-section (6).`
  line
  line `(11) The Authority may refuse to renew the registration of a farm under sub-section (10) if the`
  line `Authority is satisfied that the person to whom such registration is made has failed to utilise such farm for`
  line `coastal aquaculture purposes or without any reasonable cause has violated any provision of this Act or the`
  line `rules or regulations made there under or any direction or order made by the Authority in pursuance of`
  line `section 11:`
  line
  line `Provided that such refusal to renew the registration shall not be made without providing such person`
  line `an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.For the purposes of this section, "appointed day" means the date of establishment of`
  line `the Authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the expression "to renew the`
  line `registration" used in sub-sections (10) and (11) shall be construed to include further renewal of the`
  line registration.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
